o%20capture%20the%20enormous%20second-life%20value%20these%20batteries%20can%20offer%20before%20they're%20recycled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20Redwood%20processes%20more%20than%2020%20GWh%20of%20used%20lithium-ion%20batteries%2C%20representing%20about%20250%2C000%20EVs%2C%20or%2090%25%20of%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20recycled%20in%20North%20America.%20The%20company%20says%20most%20of%20those%20battery%20packs%20still%20retain%2050%25%20to%2080%25%20of%20their%20original%20capacity.%20While%20no%20longer%20suitable%20for%20vehicles%2C%20they're%20viable%20for%20stationary%20energy%20storage%2C%20especially%20in%20an%20era%20where%20data%20center%20energy%20needs%20are%20skyrocketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20explosion%20of%20AI%20data%20center%20construction%20around%20Redwood's%20Nevada%20campus%20paints%20the%20picture.%20These%20facilities%20demand%20more%20power%20than%20traditional%20cloud%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20the%20existing%20grid%20struggles%20to%20keep%20up.%20Enter%20Redwood%20Energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227337855f-02de-4b3a-a25e-47f810af9060%5C%22%3EReinventing%20energy%20storage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Redwood%20Materials%20energy%20storage%20system%20for%20a%20modular%20data%20center%20in%20Nevada%2C%20viewed%20from%20above%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685c682a3d5881a51c1c181f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Redwood%20Materials%20energy%20storage%20system%20for%20a%20modular%20data%20center%20in%20Nevada%2C%20viewed%20from%20above.%3Cp%3ERedwood%20Materials%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERedwood%20Energy%20aims%20to%20transform%20lightly%20used%20EV%20batteries%20into%20energy%20storage%20systems%20that%20can%20serve%20data%20centers%2C%20industrial%20customers%2C%20and%20the%20grid.%20Its%20first%20deployment%20is%20already%20live%3A%20a%20battery%20system%20with%2012